Definition.WordDefinition: Time-honored \Time"-hon`ored\ (t[imac]m"[o^]n`[~e]rd), a. Honored for a long time; venerable, and worthy of honor, by reason of antiquity, or long continuance. [1913 Webster]
time-honored adj 1: honored because of age or long usage; "time-honored institutions" [syn: {time-honoured}] 2: of long standing and acceptance; "time-honored customs" [syn: {time-honoured}]
